HEADWORD: Sylvic
<hw>Syl"vic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Of,
pertaining to, or resembling, pine or its products; specifically,
designating an acid called also <xex>abeitic acid</xex>, which is the
chief ingredient of common resin (obtained from <spn>Pinus
sylvestris</spn>, and other species).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sylvicoline</ent>⟦br⟧
